.TH UNCUT 1 "June 2026" "uncut 0.2.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
uncut \- standalone console client for the Uncutt Cards API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B uncut
.I command
[
.I target
]
[
.I options
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B uncut
is a standalone command line client for Uncutt wallet and virtual card
operations. It stores an API key locally, calls the Cards API directly, and does
not require Node.js, Go, npm, or curl at runtime.
.SH AUTH COMMANDS
.TP
.B uncut login
Prompt for an API key and save it locally.
.TP
.B uncut logout
Remove the saved API key.
.TP
.B uncut config
Show config status without printing the full key or endpoint.
.SH WALLET COMMANDS
.TP
.B uncut balance
Show wallet balance.
.TP
.B uncut deposit
Show USDT deposit addresses.
.TP
.B uncut wallet [--page N|--all]
Show wallet transaction history, newest first.
.SH CARD COMMANDS
.TP
.B uncut bins
List available card BINs, supported currencies, and fees.
.TP
.B uncut new BIN_ID [--name NAME] [--currency CODE] [--topup AMOUNT] [--3ds --phone PHONE] [--wait]
Create a new card asynchronously. Defaults: generated name, USD currency, zero
initial top-up. The command checks existing cards and refuses duplicate names
before sending the create request.
.TP
.B uncut cards [--reveal]
List cards. Without --reveal, full PAN/CVV is hidden.
.TP
.B uncut card CARD_ID [--reveal]
Show one card. With --reveal, full PAN/CVV is shown.
.TP
.B uncut topup CARD_ID --amount AMOUNT [--wait]
Move wallet funds to a card asynchronously. The amount can also be positional:
uncut topup CARD_ID AMOUNT --wait.
.TP
.B uncut withdraw CARD_ID --amount AMOUNT [--wait]
Move card funds back to wallet asynchronously.
.TP
.B uncut transactions CARD_ID [--page N|--all]
Show card transactions, newest first.
.TP
.B uncut rename CARD_ID NAME
Rename a card.
.TP
.B uncut phone CARD_ID --phone PHONE
Update the 3DS phone number.
.TP
.B uncut freeze CARD_ID
Freeze a card.
.TP
.B uncut unfreeze CARD_ID
Unfreeze a card.
.TP
.B uncut delete CARD_ID [--yes]
Close a card and refund remaining balance. Without --yes, asks for
confirmation.
.SH OPERATION COMMANDS
.TP
.B uncut operation OPERATION_ID
Show asynchronous operation status.
.TP
.B uncut wait OPERATION_ID [--interval SECONDS] [--timeout SECONDS]
Poll until an operation is completed, failed, or timed out.
.SH HELP
.TP
.B uncut help COMMAND
Show command-specific help and examples. For card and BIN commands, examples
include current account ids when available.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Print JSON instead of formatted text for API commands.
.TP
.B --reveal, --full
Reveal PAN/CVV for card commands.
.TP
.B --page N
Request a paginated page.
.TP
.B --all
Fetch all paginated pages.
.TP
.B --wait
Wait for asynchronous card creation, top-up, or withdrawal.
.TP
.B --yes
Confirm destructive actions.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help.
.TP
.B -v, --version
Show version.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B UNCUT_API_KEY
API key used before the local config file.
.TP
.B UNCUT_BASE_URL
API endpoint used before the local config file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/uncut/config.json
Local config file containing the saved API key and endpoint. It is written with
0600 permissions.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
uncut login
uncut balance
uncut deposit
uncut bins
uncut cards
uncut card card_demo_ads --reveal
uncut new bin_demo_ads --wait
uncut new bin_demo_ads --name "Facebook Ads" --currency USD --topup 25 --wait
uncut topup card_demo_ads --amount 60 --wait
uncut help topup
uncut transactions card_demo_ads --page 2
uncut delete card_demo_ads --yes
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
API or runtime error.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.TP
.B 3
Missing API key.
